  "abstract": "Pursuant to its Regulatory Planning and Review Program, the Federal Reserve Board (the ``Board'') is undertaking a review of Regulation B, which carries out the provisions of the Equal Credit Opportunity Act (the ``ECOA''). The ECOA makes it unlawful for creditors to discriminate against an applicant in any aspect of a credit transaction on the basis of race, color, religion, national origin, sex, marital status, age, and other specified bases. The review will determine whether Regulation B shou",
